Mission.Description: Ada commands a blitzkrieg to seize the gateway to the Throne world.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
for i=1,3 do GG.CAI.SuspendAI(i, true) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factorytank.id, 0) if i ~= 1 then GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryveh.id, 0) else GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factorycloak.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryshield.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryhover.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryjump.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factoryspider.id, 0) end end
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("IntroArmy1") for unitID in pairs(units) do local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {x - 2000, y, z}, 0) end
units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("IntroArmy2") for unitID in pairs(units) do local _,shieldState = Spring.GetUnitShieldState(unitID) if shieldState then Spring.SetUnitShieldState(unitID, -1, true, 3600) end local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {x + 2000, y, z}, 0) end
units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Mine") for unitID in pairs(units) do local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {x + 16, y, z}, 0) end
units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Screamer") for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.STOCKPILE, {}, { "ctrl", "shift" }) end
units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Dereg") for unitID in pairs(units) do GG.CAI.RemoveUnit(unitID) end
units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Obj") for unitID in pairs(units) do GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) end
GG.UseOrbitalStrike("kinetic_impactor", 3, 5300, 6000, 600, 15, 25) GG.UseOrbitalStrike("kinetic_impactor", 3, 5600, 5300, 600, 16, 24) GG.UseOrbitalStrike("kinetic_impactor", 3, 5450, 4550, 600, 15, 26)

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Legate Fides of the Imperial Vanguard Legion opposes you again. Neutralize his command unit.
TriggerLogic.Title: Defeat Legate Fides

TriggerLogic.Description:
Disarm the explosive charges on the ship manufacturing and storage facilities. We need them intact.
Clear all enemies around the building and place a unit in the circle to disarm each bomb.
TriggerLogic.Title: Disarm Bombs (3)

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: if WG.Music then WG.Music.SetWarThreshold(0) WG.Music.SetPeaceThreshold(-1) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: For them to have made it this far... We have no choice. Activate Thermopylae.
But, sir...
We cannot let the heretics reach the Throne world. Set the demo charges. Now.
Yes, sir.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action
Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: We'll need to start by clearing out their hill strongpoints and their deadly anti-air defenses. The hills are heavily shielded, but that's no problem for a Tremor.

TriggerLogic.Description: Neutralize both of the enemy strongpoints on the small hills in the valley. In particular, destroy the Screamer long-range SAM batteries.
TriggerLogic.Title: Destroy Strongpoints (2)

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Tremor saturates enemy defenses with a rain of inaccurate projectiles. It is ineffective against most point targets, but can wear down clumped defenses and shields in short order.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local x1, z1 = 11380, 2780 local x2, z2 = 9380, 2780 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x2, z2) + 200
for i=-1,2 do local mod = i*256 local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("gunshipheavyskirm", x1, y, z1 + mod, "s", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x1, z1 + mod) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {x2, y, z2 + mod}, 0) end

TriggerLogic.Message: Excellent. Now our Brawler gunships will have free reign over much of the battlefield.
The high-flying Brawler gunship cuts down enemies with its autoguns while staying out of the range of most ground weapons. Its armor lets it survive a modest amount of anti-air fire.
Air transports can get our units to the front line faster. I'm making some available now.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local x1, z1 = 12240, 1600 local x2, z2 = 9080, 2780 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x2, z2) + 200
for i=0,1 do local mod = i*128 local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("gunshipheavytrans", x1 + mod, y, z1 + mod, "s", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x1 + mod, z1 + mod) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {x2 + mod, y, z2 + mod}, 0) end

TriggerLogic.Message:
Air transports can be used to ferry newly built units quickly to the front lines, or to insert them behind enemy defenses. The smaller Valkyrie transport can only carry one of certain lighter units, while the Vindicator can lift almost any unit in the game (albeit one at a time), and also comes with guns.
There are several ways to use transports: 1) Manual load (default hotkey L) and unload (default U). Click and drag to issue as an area command. 2) Transport AI. Idle transports will automatically fly units fresh out of a factory to the fac's rally point, if it's faster than walking. 3) Ferry routes. With the command active, click to set start point, shift+click for waypoints, click to set end point. Click on an existing start point to remove the route, shift+click a point to move it. Move transports and passengers into the start point to assing them to the route. 4) Embark/disembark. This one is quite complex; consult the manual.
If a transport is destroyed, whatever it was carrying falls to the ground, potentially hitting anything underneath for damage.
I've stolen something very useful from the Imperial databanks. The Goliath tank buster is now available to you, Ada.

The Goliath is a slow, muscular beast designed to smash lesser assault units and other single targets into oblivion with its heavy tankbuster cannon. Supporting it is a slowing beam that helps it incapacitate its prey.
I won't lose to you here...

You've already lost, Fides. You lost when you gave up your will to a god whom you've never seen and yet rules over every aspect of your life like a tin-pot dictator. Don't worry, I'll put an end to this soon enough.
SILENCE! I will yet kill you where you stand, rebel!
One bomb defused.
Please be more careful, friend Ada. We can't afford to lose you at this critical junction.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: The barbarians shall not pass. The Empire lives on.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: That a former soldier of the Empire would fall so far as to be leading the barbarians into her heart... You foul this very planet with your presence, Ada Caedmon!
The Empire I served is dead. The Empire you serve is but a shambling ghoul that needs to be put down.
Words will not save you today, traitor. This valley of death shall be your grave.
I have no need of words, Legate.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: if GG.mission.counters["Fidus Dead"] ~= 1 then GG.mission.SetTriggerEnabledByName("Fidus Dialogue 2", true) end

local fidusID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Fidus") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(fidusID, true) Spring.SetUnitHealth(fidusID, {paralyze = 999999}) GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(fidusID, true) Spring.SetUnitPosition(fidusID, x, z) Spring.MoveCtrl.Enable(fidusID) -- clear impulse Spring.MoveCtrl.Disable(fidusID) --Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) --Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) --Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") --Spring.DestroyUnit(fidusID, false, true)
-- clear attack commands on the now-dead Fidus local units = Spring.GetUnitsInCylinder(x, z, 700)
local blankTable = {} for i=1,#units do local unitID = units[i] local queue = Spring.GetUnitCommands(unitID, 1) or blankTable local cmd = queue[1] if cmd and cmd.id == CMD.ATTACK and cmd.params[1] == fidusID then Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.REMOVE, {cmd.tag}, 0) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, 34924, blankTable, 0) -- cancel target Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.WAIT, blankTable, 0) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.WAIT, blankTable, 0) end end
local units = Spring.GetTeamUnits(0) for i=1,#units do GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(units[i], true) end

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Fidus") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) x = x + math.random(-15, 15) z = z + math.random(-15, 15) y = y + math.random(-20, 20) Spring.SpawnCEG("babette", x, y, z)

TriggerLogic.Message: To have been defeated... by one such as you...
Goodbye, Legate. You were a good soldier; it's too bad you couldn't have been something more than that.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = Spring.GetTeamUnits(0) for i=1,#units do GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(units[i], false) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Please make haste, Ada. We have little time remaining.
Taking out that Moho Geothermal Powerplant could save us a lot of trouble with disabling the defense grid.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: That Moho Geothermal powerplant provides a considerable amount of energy for the enemy's war machine and contributes power to their defense grid. Destroy it to set the enemy back considerably.
TriggerLogic.Title: Destroy Moho Geo (Optional)

TriggerLogic.Message: Excellent. Things should get a little easier for us now.
Please be careful with that thing, Ada. If it goes up, it'll take the whole neighbourhood with it.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Singularity Reactor provides huge amounts of energy at near-unparalleled metal efficiency. It is also a very expensive, very desirable target, and if it gets destroyed, the resulting explosion is comparable to a nuclear weapon.
One of the target buildings has just gone up in smoke. We won't have the resources to take the Throne world now.
